main event: A civilian reported observing an object hovering and moving in a zig-zag course for several miles above Palmer, Alaska on February 11, 1952.
interesting points: The object was first observed hovering approximately 500 feet above ground level,The sighting lasted approximately 15 minutes,It was concluded that the object was an astronomical body,It was characterized by reflecting movement or light,There were multiple reports of unusual phenomena in the area from various civilians.
sighted object: an unidentified object in the sky
